vb. 3ae weak (1) create, beget human beings, Sin. R8; B72; Pr. 7, 10; ir , fem. irt n, ‘engendered by’, in filiations, Gr. §§ 361.379, 3; make, construct concrete things, Sin. B17.305; Les. 70, 17; 71, 4-6; Urk. IV, 207, 11; 437, 4.13; xsbD iryt ‘artificial lapis-lazuli’, Urk. IV, 701, 2; make decrees, laws, written documents, Siut, pl. 6, 260; P. Kah. 11, 10; Mill. 1, 1; Eb. 1, 9; Urk. IV, 1045,4; ir m sS ‘put into writing’, Urk. IV, 1111, 15; 1112, 4; abstracts, e.g. trouble, Peas. B1, 98.102; a (fair) name, B1, 64; similarly Sin. B299; Urk. V, 104, 6; M. u. K. 2, 3; Pr. 7, 9; actions, e.g. an assault, Sin. B101; a flight, B277; a noise, Westc. 12, 3; similarly Sin. B192; Sh. S. 55; Les. 71, 13; Urk. IV, 5, 7; 194, 15.
(2) do: (a) with obj., e. g. good, Sin. B74-5; evil, Les. 69, 22; justice, Peas. B1, 68; iry·i m ‘What can I do?’, Adm. 2, 9; similarly Westc. 11, 6; Sin. B183; Adm. 3, 7; ir ib ‘do the will of’, P. Kah. 34, 2-4; ir aHaw ‘do attendance on’, Sin. B282-3; ir wpt ‘do business’, Sin. B117; Pr. 7, 3; JEA 4, pl. 8, 7; ir wpt Hna ‘punish’, L. to D. IV, 4-5 (n.); ir Hr ‘do the bidding of’, JEA 4; pl. 8, 9, cf. p. 34, n. 7; ir Hst ‘do the pleasure of’, Peas. B1, 3; D. el. B. 107; cf. GES 9: (b) without obj. ‘do (anything)’, L. to D. II, 4; D4-M17-M17 ‘I will do so’, answer to order or request, D. el. B. 107; irr Hm·k m mrr·f ‘Your Majesty will do as you wish’, Sin. B236; ‘the land turns round mi irr nHp as does a potter’s wheel’, Adm. 2, 8.
(3) act, take action, Peas. B1, 156; B2, 124; act as, in the capacity of, an official, etc., Westc. 9, 12; Pr. 5, 3; Sh. S. 183; Peas. B1, 128-30; Urk. IV, 545, 7; exercise on office, Westc. 9, 11; Sin. B235; Les. 72, 12; Urk. I, 106, 9; appoint officials, Peas. B1, 296; Urk. IV, 1112, 9.
(4) achieve a result or purpose, Mill. 1, 3; Westc. 4, 11-12; Sin. B52.203.
(5) in medical context: prepare a remedy, P. Kah. 5, 14; Eb. 38, 6; apply a remedy, Eb. 46, 10; treat an ailment, Rec. Champ. 401.
(6) in mathematical context: ir aAy x r y ‘work out the excess of x over y’, P. Kah. 8, 51-2; ir x sp y ‘multiply x by y’, 8, 34; ir x ‘square x’, JEA 15, pl. 36, 14, 4-6. (7) used pregnantly, succeed, Pr. 8, 5; make prosperous, maintain, L. to D. VI, 8 (n.).
(8) various: lay out a garden, Sin. B305; similarly Urk. IV, 73, 10; cultivate crops, JEA 16, 69; perform a miracle, Westc. 11, 11; a dance, Sin. B194; prepare food and drink, BH I, 8, 20; Sin. B87; garner corn, Urk. VI, 743, 1; read aloud a book, BD 497, 12; recite a spell, M. u. K. 6, 7; spend, pass time, Sin. B29; Sh. S. 41; Peas. B1, 31; Westc. 2, 6; celebrate a festival, Les. 70, 7; Urk. IV, 199, 10; traverse lands, GNS 97; conduct an expedition, JEA 35, 48; inflict a wound, L. to D. V, 1; marshal a force, Bull. 30, 101; ir m ‘be busy with’, Ikhekhi, p. 44; ir sp Hna ‘deal with’, Pr. 14, 7; similarly 14, 9; ir kAt m ‘adopt a profession as’, Les. 83, 2. For various technical or idiomatic uses not included above, c. g. ir irw ‘levy a tax’, see under the second element.
